 *
 *   In the parent component:
 *   .ds.parent { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); }
 *
 *   In this component:
 *   :host                { display: grid; grid-column: span 2; }
 *   .ds.<%= kebabName %> { display: grid; grid-template-columns: subgrid; }
 *
 *   In this example, the parent establishes a 4-column grid.
 *   This component claims 2 of those columns and inherits their widths via subgrid.
 *
 * Keep in mind:
 *   - Custom elements are display: inline by default — always set display on :host.
 *   - Flex/grid rules only affect direct children of the container, not deeper descendants.
 *   - External CSS cannot pierce the shadow boundary — expose CSS custom properties for theming.
 */

